@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node FAQ.Hard_Drives.2.14 "Hard_Drives Questions"
@toc FAQ.Hard_Drives

    2.14 What is an auto-booting hard drive?

            Until Workbench 1.3, the Amiga did not have auto booting
        hard drives. They required a floppy disk based program to
        commence the hard drive mounting and booting. Newer file
        systems and the RDB structure permit auto booting and auto
        mounting hard disks.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
